-- Sistema’s Indian Unit Receives 12.8 Billion Rupee Loan
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-01-12T11:56:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/sistema-s-indian-unit-gets-12-8-billion-rupee-loan-for-8-years.html
Sistema Shyam TeleServices Ltd., an
Indian unit of Russian billionaire  Vladimir Yevtushenkov ’s  AFK
Sistema (AFKS) , received a 12.8 billion rupee ($247 million) loan
organized by  Deutsche Bank AG. (DBK)   The loan was provided in the form of nonconvertible bonds
and is for eight years, Moscow-based Sistema said in an e-mailed
statement today. It didn’t disclose the interest rate.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
